# CF Ladder Pro - Environment Variables

# ============================================
# GENERAL
# ============================================
NODE_ENV=production

# ============================================
# NEXT.JS
# ============================================
# Next.js automatically uses these
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://your-domain.vercel.app

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL: Error Monitoring (Recommended for Production)
# ============================================
# Uncomment and add your Sentry DSN if using error monitoring
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=your_sentry_dsn_here
# SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=your_sentry_auth_token

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL: Redis Rate Limiting (For Multi-Instance Scaling)
# ============================================
# Uncomment if upgrading to Redis-based rate limiting
# KV_REST_API_URL=your_vercel_kv_url
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=your_vercel_kv_token

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL: Email Service (Bug Reports via Gmail)
# ============================================
# Create a Gmail App Password: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# GMAIL_USER=your-email@gmail.com
# GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=your-16-char-app-password
# REPORT_RECIPIENT=your-email@gmail.com  # defaults to GMAIL_USER if not set

# ============================================
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# ============================================
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local for local development
# 2. Add variables to Vercel project settings for production
# 3. Never commit .env.local to version control
# 4. Restart dev server after changing environment variables

# ============================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================
# - No API keys are required for basic functionality
# - Codeforces API is public and doesn't require authentication
# - Add API keys only if integrating additional services
# - Always use environment variables for sensitive data
# - Never hardcode API keys in source code
